    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Barry Jay and the Historical Commission are currently restoring the historic signs that mark Marlboro’s landmarks, making it a great time to visit.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://patch.com/new-jersey/marlboro-coltsneck/visit-marlboros-historic-landmarks"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Morganville sits in northern Monmouth County, just north of Marlboro Township’s center.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        11
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morganville%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "New Jersey Route 79 cuts through Morganville, linking the community to Matawan to the north and Freehold to the south.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morganville%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Mount Pleasant, rising to 364 feet, dominates the southeast part of Morganville’s landscape.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morganville%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "Water from Morganville drains north via Gravelly Brook toward Matawan Creek and west via Deep Run toward the South River.",
